## Upgrade Strategy

### Phase 1: Safe Upgrades (patch/minor within same major)
Run `npm update` to pick up semver-compatible updates. Run test suite. If green, commit.

Packages: @emotion/*, axios, swr, socket.io-client, node-mailjet, react-hook-form, react-hot-toast, react-select, react-textarea-autosize, react-tooltip, react-use-measure, styled-components, postcss, autoprefixer, jsonwebtoken

### Phase 2: Major Upgrades (one branch per package)
Order by risk, lowest first:
1. mongodb 6→7
2. react-icons 4→5
3. react-hotkeys-hook 4→5
4. iron-session 6→8
5. bcryptjs 2→3
6. stripe 15→22
7. Next.js 13→14 (then 14→15)
8. React 18→19
9. tailwindcss 3→4

Per upgrade: branch → install → build → test suite → PR

### Lock File
Use `package-lock.json` (npm). Delete `yarn.lock` if it exists.
